<tr><td></td><td>LOCATION--Ship's theatre</td></tr>
<tr id="L1"><td><a href="#L1">1</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: A production of a scene from Cyrano de Bergerac, with Reginald Barclay in the title role and Beverly Crusher as Roxanne</td></tr>

<tr id="L2"><td><a href="#L2">2</a></td><td>CRUSHER:  You were like a brother to me. Do you remember? We used played in the park near the lake.</td></tr>

<tr id="L3"><td><a href="#L3">3</a></td><td>BARCLAY:  Yes, of course. Every summer, you came to Bergerac.</td></tr>

<tr id="L4"><td><a href="#L4">4</a></td><td>CRUSHER:  You used to make swords out of the reeds, and when you cut your hand you would come running to me, and I would say, Let me see. Oh! How did you do that?</td></tr>

<tr id="L5"><td><a href="#L5">5</a></td><td>BARCLAY:  Playing near the Porte de Nesle.</td></tr>

<tr id="L6"><td><a href="#L6">6</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: he catches his hat on the scenery and it comes off</td></tr>

<tr id="L7"><td><a href="#L7">7</a></td><td>CRUSHER:  And how many did you plat against?</td></tr>

<tr id="L8"><td><a href="#L8">8</a></td><td>BARCLAY:  No more than a hundred.</td></tr>

<tr id="L9"><td><a href="#L9">9</a></td><td>CRUSHER:  Tell me!</td></tr>

<tr id="L10"><td><a href="#L10">10</a></td><td>BARCLAY:  No.</td></tr>

<tr id="L11"><td><a href="#L11">11</a></td><td>CRUSHER:  (sotto, prompting) Let it go.</td></tr>

<tr id="L12"><td><a href="#L12">12</a></td><td>BARCLAY:  (sotto) What?</td></tr>

<tr id="L13"><td><a href="#L13">13</a></td><td>CRUSHER:  (sotto) Let it go.</td></tr>

<tr id="L14"><td><a href="#L14">14</a></td><td>BARCLAY:  Let it go. Let it go. You tell me what you were going to say. Do you dare?</td></tr>

<tr id="L15"><td><a href="#L15">15</a></td><td>CRUSHER:  I do dare. I love someone.</td></tr>

<tr id="L16"><td><a href="#L16">16</a></td><td>BARCLAY:  Ah!</td></tr>

<tr id="L17"><td><a href="#L17">17</a></td><td>CRUSHER:  He does not know.</td></tr>

<tr id="L18"><td><a href="#L18">18</a></td><td>BARCLAY:  Ah!</td></tr>

